                    "body": "Scheduling for 1.0.3",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-16T14:33:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-16T14:33:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17655",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I suspect the OP was using an old version of ZF at the time of reporting. Currently, initView() calls $view->getScriptPaths() to set $currentPaths, which always returns an array. No fix is necessary at this time.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-20T09:52:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-20T09:52:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17666",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=php_beach",
                        "name": "php_beach",
                        "displayName": "Dennis Fogg",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Nope, I was not using an old version of ZF.  \nI was using ZF 1.0.1 when I encountered this problem.  Also, I upgraded to ZF 1.0.2 and still had this problem.\n\nNote, however, that I use Smarty for my views.\nI use the code labeled: \"As an example, the following is one potential wrapper for Smarty:\"  at \nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.view.scripts.html#zend.view.scripts.templates \nand also the integration method from \nhttp:\/\/www.nabble.com\/Re%3A-Demo-application--p12186729s16154.html\n\nI can upload my file if you need it but I would have to clean it up a bit.\n\nSo, I think the bug is still there for Smarty views.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=php_beach",
                        "name": "php_beach",
                        "displayName": "Dennis Fogg",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-21T02:35:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-21T02:35:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17671",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'll make a note that I need to fix the example in the docs, but as that is not a part of the official distribution -- i.e., it's not a class we distribute with Framework -- I consider this a relatively minor issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-21T08:57:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-21T08:57:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17672",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=php_beach",
                        "name": "php_beach",
                        "displayName": "Dennis Fogg",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think this is an important (and easy) fix because anyone who tries to use zend framework and smarty (using the current ZF docs) will run into this:\n\n\nERRNO: 2 \nTEXT: Invalid argument supplied for foreach() \nLOCATION: C:\\...\\zend_framework_head\\Zend\\Controller\\Action\\Helper\\ViewRenderer.php, line 322, at November 22, 2007, 12:18 am\nShowing backtrace:\nZend_Controller_Action_Helper_ViewRenderer.initView() # line  350, file: C:\\...\\zend_framework_head\\Zend\\Controller\\Action\\Helper\\ViewRenderer.php\nZend_Controller_Action_Helper_ViewRenderer.init() # line  136, file: C:\\...\\zend_framework_head\\Zend\\Controller\\Action\\HelperBroker.php\nZend_Controller_Action_HelperBroker.__construct(Object:indexController) # line  128, file: C:\\...\\zend_framework_head\\Zend\\Controller\\Action.php\nZend_Controller_Action.__construct(Object:Zend_Controller_Request_Http, Object:Zend_Controller_Response_Http, Array[0]) # line  214, file: C:\\...\\zend_framework_head\\Zend\\Controller\\Dispatcher\\Standard.php\nZend_Controller_Dispatcher_Standard.dispatch(Object:Zend_Controller_Request_Http, Object:Zend_Controller_Response_Http) # line  920, file: C:\\...\\zend_framework_head\\Zend\\Controller\\Front.php\nZend_Controller_Front.dispatch() # line  119, file: C:\\...\\run.php\nrequire(\"C:\\...\\...\") # line   15, file: C:\\...\\index.php\n\n\nand then they have to roll up their sleeves and start debugging instead of learning how to use the controller -- it's an unpleasent user experience for newbies!\n\nUsing the tip from earlier comments, I think the fix is a 1 line change in the documentation for the sample Smarty class for Zend_View:\nIn the function getScriptPaths():\nreplace:\nreturn $this->_smarty->template_dir;\nwith:\nreturn array($this->_smarty->template_dir);\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=php_beach",
                        "name": "php_beach",
                        "displayName": "Dennis Fogg",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-22T02:57:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-22T02:57:47.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
